The first matches in the Limpopo Impala Cricket Union’s promotional league start this Sunday. Two Louis Trichardt-based teams will be competing at their home venues in the first round. At the LTT Oval, the Louis Trichardt Cricket Club will test their strength against the University of Limpopo’s side. On the same day, the Eltivillas club will play against the Phalaborwa Elephants Cricket Club. The matches start at 09:45. In the other clashes, Mahwelereng Vultures will play against Nkowankowa at Mahwelereng. Stars will play against Nashua Aces in Nirvana and Phalaborwa CC will meet Seshego CC at Impala Park. Giyani CC will travel to Polokwane to play against Nirvana CC.